The standard is proposed by National Audit Office of the People's Republic of China.
This part is under the jurisdiction of the National Technical Committee 341 on Audit_IT of Standardi zation Administration of China (SAC/TC 341).
This part is drafted by: IT Center, National Audit Office of the People's Republic of China, Yonyou Software Co. Ltd (UFIDA).

Drafting units: INSPUR Shandong common software Group Ltd., Kingdee Software (China) Co., Ltd., Oracle (China) Software System Co., Ltd., Nanjing Audit University, Guangdong Provincial Audit Department, Hangzhou New grand Software Co., Ltd., Chongqing eAbax Software Limited, SAP (Beijing) Software System Co., Ltd., China Electronics Standardization Institute.

This part is firstly released in 06/2010.
Financial Information Technology--Data Interface of Accounting

This standard specifies the format requirements of accounting software interface data, including accounting data elements, data interface output file content and format in accordance with Enterprise Accounting Standards released by the Ministry of Finance of the People's Republic of China on February 15, 2006 and Basic Norms of Internal Control released on June 26, 2008.
This section applies to enterprises that use accounting software design, development, management,

The following files are essential to the application of this document. Among the dated reference documents, only the dated version is applicable to this document. About every undated reference document, the latest version (including all the modification lists) is applicable to this document.
GB / T 2261.1-2003 Basic personal information classification and code Part I: Human Gender Codes GB / T 4754 Classification of the national economy
GB / T 7408-2005 Data elements and interchange formats - Information interchange dates and time format (ISO 8601: 2000, IDT)
GB 11714-1997 Coding rules for national organization
GB / T 12406-2008 Codes for the representation of currencies and funds (ISO 4217: 2001, IDT) GB 18030-2005 Information technology - Chinese coded character set
GB / T 18142-2000 Information technology data element values format Notation (ISO / IEC 14957: 1996, IDT)
GB / T 18793-2002 Information technology - Extensible Markup Language (XML) 1.0
The following terms and definitions can be applied to this document.
It is a computer application software for accounting work.
The interface between the computer software systems in transferring data and exchanging information is realized in the format of electronic document.
3.3  XML File Extensible Markup Language File
Data file is described by the extensible markup language with the function of data description, high structure and verifiability.
It is the file used for the exchange or processing of accounting data.
It is a data unit using a set of attributes to describe definition, identification, indication, and allowable values.
Notes: In this part, data elements are indivisible basic units of the output data of data interface of ERP
The internal structure of the output data of the data interface of ERP software includes several different data elements.

It is an accounting unit to record a collection of data used by computer accounts of electronic documents. It is generated through accounting by using accounting software and stored in a computer storage device or media.

Subsidiary accounting is the subdivision of financial information from different angles.With a combination of accounts, it can fully reflect the business transaction, make accounting processing more flexible , and give full play to the advantages of computerized accounting.
4.1  Rules of Describing The Data Elements
It describes the format of data elements as follows:

a) Identifier of data elements: By this standard, it is the unique identifier for each data element marked by six digits. The first two are element category number, the third and the fourth are the data table number in this category , and the last two are the order number after the standardized combination of the elements. It will not be repeatedly numbered if it has been already numbered in some table. In this part, the first two digits indicate the following classification:
b) Name of data elements: Chinese name of data elements ;
c) Description of data elements: a description of the meaning of data elements;
d) Indication of data elements: the representation of category and length of the data element value, according to the requirements of GB / T 18142-2000, specifically as follows:
-- C indicates numbers, letters, characters and other characters, etc.
-- C n indicates an n-bit fixed-length character
e) Notes of the data element: Additional Notes associated with the data elements.
